    choose "Android Basics in Kotlin", 
      https://developer.android.com/courses/android-basics-kotlin/course

      6 units: "Unit 1: Kotlin basics", "Unit 2: Layouts", "3 Navigation", 
                 "4 Connect to the internet", "5 Data persistence", "6 WorkManager"

      Unit 1: "pathway 1 introduction to kotlin", "pathway 2 create your first app", 
                "3 build a basic layout", "4 add a button to an app", 
                all dated May 2020.

      choose "pathway 3 Build a basic layout". 
        https://developer.android.com/courses/pathways/android-basics-kotlin-three

          Use: "Empty Activity" template.
          Use: name "Greeting 1 App", package "com.example.greeting1app", location "Greeting1App", 
               lang "Kotlin", min sdk "API 23: Android 6.0 (Marshmallow)".
               uncheck "Use legacy android support libraries". 

          Tips: set adb path when it cannot detect the adb path
                 "Extended controls (...) > Settings > General tab > 'Use detected ADB location'"
          Concepts: view, viewGroup, textView, ConstraintLayout

          Work through the part with a TextView and its layout. 
          Skip the part for an ImageView.

      choose "pathway 4 Add a button to an app". 

          Tips: auto import or alt-enter
          Concepts: class and object in kotlin
                    string resource in string.xml
                    activities
                    button
                    toast: 
                        val rollButton: Button = findViewById(R.id.button)
                        rollButton.setOnClickListener {
                            val toast = Toast.makeText(this, "Dice Rolled!", Toast.LENGTH_SHORT)
                            toast.show()
                        }
                    if else when Boolean
                    image
                    unit test
                    debugging with log



